communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This rejection of the sale of cattle has been going on for over a month in
Bangladesh and will have a major impact on the farmers for some time to
come, certainly until the public have regained confidence in the safety of
the meat that they buy in shops and markets. Members are encouraged to read
the original article, which has an excellent picture of camels as well as
an interesting commentary.

A somewhat angry article in the Sri Lanka Guardian commenting on the
political aspects can be read at
<http://www.srilankaguardian.org/2010/11/anthrax-and-eid-ul-azha.html>.

All in all this reinforces the view that disease outbreaks should not be
seen as mere biological events. They take place in a social and economic
environment and with wide impacts. - Mod.MHJ

For maps of Bangladesh, go to
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/bangladesh_rel96.jpg>
and <http://healthmap.org/r/00Sn>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
